---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About - DocDriven"
  description="Learn about the author of DocDriven and the context behind this structured methodology."
  lang="en"
>
  <main class="about">
    <section class="about-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>About DocDriven</h1>
        <p class="hero-subtitle">
          Open source methodology for structured software development with LLMs
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-content">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="content-grid">
          <div class="main-content">
            <h2>The Author</h2>
            <h3>Eric Gauthier</h3>
            <p>
              Senior software architect with 30+ years of experience in designing complex systems,
              I developed DocDriven to address a pragmatic observation: ad-hoc adoption of
              Large Language Models in software development generates invisible technical debt that
              only manifests months after implementation.
            </p>

            <p>
              My career has allowed me to observe the evolution of development methodologies, from
              Waterfall to Agile, from TDD to DevOps. The emergence of LLMs represents a change as
              fundamental as the adoption of IDEs or automated refactoring. However, without a
              rigorous methodological framework, this powerful tool becomes a generator of accidental complexity.
            </p>

            <h2>Genesis of DocDriven</h2>
            <p>
              DocDriven is not an academic theory. This methodology was developed and tested
              on a real complex data processing project (Chef Jules), where each phase was
              empirically validated. The result: 840 generated tests, zero regressions, and a
              Fagan score of 85/100 in final inspection.
            </p>

            <p>
              The methodology structures LLM adoption through 6 distinct phases where humans
              control strategic and architectural decisions (Phases 1-2, Phase 6), while
              AI accelerates tactical execution under continuous supervision (Phases 3-5). This
              clear separation of responsibilities avoids two pitfalls: over-automation (delegating
              everything to AI) and under-utilization (using AI as mere autocomplete).
            </p>

            <h2>Author/Methodology Separation</h2>
            <p>
              DocDriven is designed as an open source methodology larger than its creator.
              It belongs to the community of developers who adopt it, test it, and contribute
              to its evolution. My role is that of principal contributor, not "guru" or exclusive owner.
            </p>

            <p>
              The CC BY-SA 4.0 license ensures DocDriven remains free to use while preserving
              attribution. You are encouraged to adapt it to your specific contexts, critique it,
              and propose improvements.
            </p>

            <h2>Contact & Links</h2>
            <div class="contact-links">
              <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/eric-gauthier" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="contact-link">
                <span class="link-icon">🔗</span>
                LinkedIn
              </a>
              <a href="https://github.com/egauthier" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="contact-link">
                <span class="link-icon">💻</span>
                GitHub
              </a>
              <a href="mailto:m.e.gauthier@gmail.com" class="contact-link">
                <span class="link-icon">📧</span>
                Email
              </a>
            </div>

            <div class="about-footer-note">
              <p>
                <strong>Note:</strong> DocDriven is an actively developed methodology (V1.0).
                Your feedback and contributions are essential for its improvement. See the
                <a href="/en/licence">License page</a> for usage and contribution terms.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <aside class="sidebar-info">
            <div class="info-card">
              <h3>DocDriven Methodology</h3>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Version:</strong> 1.0</li>
                <li><strong>License:</strong> CC BY-SA 4.0</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> 15K+ words</li>
                <li><strong>ADRs:</strong> 26 decisions</li>
                <li><strong>Validation:</strong> Fagan 85/100</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="info-card">
              <h3>Quick Links</h3>
              <ul>
                <li><a href="/en/intro">Introduction</a></li>
                <li><a href="/en/phase1-architecture-strategique">Phase 1: Architecture</a></li>
                <li><a href="/en/roles-et-responsabilites">Roles & Responsibilities</a></li>
                <li><a href="/en/licence">License</a></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--dd-primary) 0%, var(--dd-neutral-dark) 100%);
    color: var(--dd-white);
    padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-6);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about-hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-family-heading);
    font-size: var(--font-size-4xl);
    color: var(--dd-white);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    color: var(--dd-secondary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .about-content {
    padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-6);
    background: var(--dd-white);
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .content-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-10);
  }

  .main-content h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-family-heading);
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
    color: var(--dd-primary);
    margin-top: var(--space-10);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    border-bottom: 3px solid var(--dd-secondary);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .main-content h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .main-content h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-family-heading);
    font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    color: var(--dd-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .main-content p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    color: var(--dd-neutral-dark);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .contact-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }

  .contact-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-5);
    background: var(--dd-secondary);
    color: var(--dd-white);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: all var(--transition-base);
  }

  .contact-link:hover {
    background: var(--dd-primary);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 12px var(--dd-shadow);
  }

  .link-icon {
    font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
  }

  .about-footer-note {
    margin-top: var(--space-10);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    background: var(--dd-neutral-light);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--dd-secondary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }

  .about-footer-note p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
  }

  .about-footer-note a {
    color: var(--dd-secondary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .sidebar-info {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .info-card {
    background: var(--dd-neutral-light);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    border-top: 4px solid var(--dd-secondary);
  }

  .info-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-family-heading);
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    color: var(--dd-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .info-card ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .info-card li {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    color: var(--dd-neutral-dark);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    line-height: var(--line-height-normal);
  }

  .info-card a {
    color: var(--dd-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .info-card a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
    color: var(--dd-primary);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-hero {
      padding: var(--space-10) var(--space-4);
    }

    .about-hero h1 {
      font-size: var(--font-size-3xl);
    }

    .about-content {
      padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-4);
    }

    .content-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .contact-links {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .contact-link {
      justify-content: center;
    }
  }
</style>
